JOHANNESBURG, South Africa, September 3, 2018/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            The Joint Constitutional Review will tomorrow hold oral presentations by stakeholders on submissions on a possible review of Section 25 of the Constitution, which would make provision for the expropriation of land without compensation. These presentations will take place at Parliament and emanate from the written submissions on the matter and will continue until Friday.





Please find the link for the draft programme https://tinyurl.com/ycyuezhf which is subject to change.





Details are as follows: 

Date: Tuesday, 04 September 2018

Time:  10:00

Venue: Committee Room Old Assembly Chamber, Ground Floor, Old Assembly Building